summary: Subventure — Bâabyâagite (Russalka’s tribe) Russalkas, the “Sewer’s Mermaids”, are a matriarcal race of proto-human amphibians...
caption:
Subventure — Bâabyâagite (Russalka’s tribe)

Russalkas, the “Sewer’s Mermaids”, are a matriarcal race of proto-human amphibians from the underground. They have four tribe, each for one of the Frog-Mothers.

Bâabyâagites descend from the Frog-Mother Bâabyâag. They are tall, thin and pale, and haunts the most secluded parts of the Underground Swamp, crawling in nomadic houseboats made of wood, clay and rubbish. Bâabyâagites are not the strongest, nor the fastest or the stealthiest. But they have a strong connexion to the supernatural, and have a genetic predilection to be psychics. Their matriarchs have shown telekinetic and telepathic abilities, but also the means to bend souls or even time and space. This makes them particularly dangerous, and they have a reputation akin to witches (although “magic” as a ritualistic practice doesn’t exist in Subventure).

Bâabyâagites carry their tadpoles on their backs, in small clay houses. Contrarily to the other tribes, their society doesn’t outright eliminate male children. They contain them in different “clayhouse”, which is filled with poisoned water. This poison render the male tadpoles infertile and alter the growth of their nervous system, basically making them braindead. Those who survive this treatment (approximatively 20%) grow to be mindless slaves to their own mothers, acting as drones and minions. Allegedly, this is the reason that made one of their tribe, Vaziliza the Kind, leave the Swamps with a dozen of stolen “clayhouses” to save the kids. This was the origin of the Vodians…

In the game, players can incarnate a Vodian, a civilized cousin race of the Russalkas. This characters can choose a lineage to one of the tribes and inherit some special traits. Vodian of Bâabyâagite’s descent have an affinity for Supernatural, they gain +5 in this stat, and can choose an additional psychic proficiency.
